 überlagerten oder sie vermischten sich mit den Rechten indigener Völker. Lange Zeit wurde diese Geschichte als Verlängerung der europäischen Rechtsgeschichte interpretiert. Dieser Band führt in die Forschungsgeschichte, deren Leistungen und Problematik ein. Er gibt eine Übersicht über wichtige Quellen und Literatur und zeigt Perspektiven der Forschung auf.  aFrom the sixteenth century, the Spanish monarchy ruled over a giant area in North, Central, and South America. Norms, institutions, and practices from Europe were translated into the world that was new to the invaders, either suppressing or mixing with the rights of Indigenous peoples. This volume provides an introduction to this chapter of legal history, provides an overview of the sources and literature, and reveals research perspectives.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 4aIndigene Völker. 4aKolonialgeschichte. 4aLateinamerika. 4aRechtswissenschaft. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / Central America.2bisacsh  aIndigenous peoples.  aLatin America.  aLaw.  acolonial history.1 aEgío, José Luis, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022z9783110992939oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831104001820 cprintz978311037973040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311037974740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110379747423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110379747/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter